  "verse": 3,
  "sanskrit": "त्याज्यं दोषवदित्येके कर्म प्राहुर्मनीषिण: |\nयज्ञदानतप:कर्म न त्याज्यमिति चापरे ||",
  "transliteration": "tyājyaṁ doṣhavad ity eke karma prāhur manīṣhiṇaḥ\nyajña-dāna-tapaḥ-karma na tyājyam iti chāpare",
  "translation": "Some learned persons declare that all action should be abandoned as faulty, while others say that acts of sacrifice, charity, and austerity should not be given up.",
