    <p><strong>2. Beyond Attachment — ‘kuśhale nānuṣhajjate’:</strong> Similarly, there is no attachment to pleasant action. The individual does not cling to favorable conditions or seek repetition of enjoyable experiences. This balance prevents dependence on external circumstances.</p>

