    <p><strong>2. Nature of the Vision — ‘atyadbhutam’:</strong> The form is described as exceedingly wondrous (<em>aty-adbhutam</em>), indicating its transcendence beyond ordinary perception. It challenges conventional categories of understanding, revealing a dimension of reality that cannot be fully captured by language or thought. This encounter expands the boundaries of perception, opening the mind to new possibilities.</p>

